Let me instead expand \( (1 + iz)^{2023} \) and \( (1 - iz)^{2023} \) using the binomial theorem. \( (1 + iz)^{2023} = \sum_{k=0}^{2023} \binom{2023}{k} (iz)^k = \sum_{k=0}^{2023} \binom{2023}{k} i^k z^k \) Similarly, \( (1 - iz)^{2023} = \sum_{k=0}^{2023} \binom{2023}{k} (-iz)^k = \sum_{k=0}^{2023} \binom{2023}{k} (-i)^k z^k \) Subtracting these two: \( (1 + iz)^{2023} - (1 - iz)^{2023} = \sum_{k=0}^{2023} \binom{2023}{k} [i^k - (-i)^k] z^k \) Note that when k is even, \( (-i)^k = (i)^k \), so the terms cancel.
